  "id": "many_secrets_known",
  "title": "The Weight of Knowing",
  "description": "You carry so many secrets that you've lost track of which truths you can speak aloud.",
  "content": "You know things. So many things. Who's betraying whom. What's really happening behind closed doors. The hidden motivations, the buried scandals, the carefully constructed lies. Every conversation is a minefield—you have to remember who knows what, who's pretending not to know, what you're supposed to know and what you absolutely cannot reveal you know. The knowledge was power once. Now it just feels like weight.",
