      "id": "selective_forgetting",
      "text": "Start deliberately forgetting some secrets",
      "description": "Not all knowledge is worth carrying.",
      "resultText": "You consciously begin letting go of secrets that don't serve anyone by being remembered. The gossip, the petty betrayals, the information you acquired just because you could—you release it. It feels like weakening yourself at first, voluntarily giving up power. But the lightness that comes with it is undeniable. You keep the secrets that matter, that protect people, and let the rest dissolve. Wisdom, you realize, includes knowing what not to know.",
